<Layout
	title="About Morris IT Consulting - Veteran-Owned Security Solutions"
	description="Meet James Morris, CISSP - Former USAF veteran with over a decade of experience in IT security, offering enterprise-grade security solutions for businesses of all sizes."
	pubDate={new Date('March 26, 2025')}
	heroImage="/about-hero.png"
>
	<div class="about-section">
		<h2>Veteran-Owned. Security-Focused. Results-Driven.</h2>
		
		<p>
			With over a decade of experience in cybersecurity and IT infrastructure, I bring military precision and enterprise-grade security expertise to businesses of all sizes. As the founder of Morris IT Consulting, I leverage my background as a United States Air Force veteran and senior security engineer to deliver robust, compliant, and innovative technology solutions.
		</p>
		
		<h3>Military-Grade Security Experience</h3>
		<p>
			During my seven years of active duty with the United States Air Force, I engineered and implemented advanced security systems worth over $5 million, protecting critical infrastructure across multiple installations. This foundation in physical and digital security shaped my methodical approach to identifying vulnerabilities and implementing comprehensive protection strategies.
		</p>
		
		<h3>Enterprise Security Leadership</h3>
		<p>
			Following my military service, I've led security initiatives for Fortune 500 corporations and federal enterprises, architecting cloud security solutions, implementing SIEM systems, and ensuring compliance with the industry's most rigorous standards including NIST, FedRAMP, and Azure Security Benchmark. My experience spans the entire security lifecycle - from threat detection and incident response to security architecture and risk management.
		</p>
		
		<h3>Credentials That Matter</h3>
		<p>
			As a Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP) with multiple Microsoft and CompTIA certifications, I maintain the highest standards of security knowledge and ethical practice. My technical expertise includes:
		</p>
		
